    "faqs": {
      "type": "accordion",
      "settings": {
        "eyebrow": "FAQs",
        "eyebrow_uppercase": true,
        "title": "Questions we get a lot.",
        "description": "",
        "heading_alignment": "center",
        "style": "separated",
        "allow_multiple": false,
        "sidebar_position": "end",
        "color_scheme": "standard-primary",
        "top_spacing": "auto",
        "bottom_spacing": "auto"
      },
      "blocks": {
        "q-1": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does flat-rate pricing work?",
            "answer": "<p>Before we start any repair, we give you a written price for the job — labor, parts, everything. If the diagnosis turns out to be different than expected, we stop and re-quote before touching anything else. You never see a surprise number on the final invoice.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q-2": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What's the warranty on your repairs?",
            "answer": "<p>Two years or 24,000 miles, whichever comes first, on both parts and labor. That's our warranty — not a manufacturer's pass-through. If something we replaced fails inside that window, we fix it at no charge, including labor.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q-3": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do I need an appointment?",
            "answer": "<p>For most jobs, yes — it lets us have the right tech and the right parts ready, and usually means same-day turnaround. Walk-ins for oil changes and quick inspections are welcome when the lobby schedule allows; call ahead to confirm.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q-4": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I get an estimate before I drop off?",
            "answer": "<p>For common jobs (oil change, brake pads, battery, alignment) we can quote on the phone or online in under five minutes. For anything that needs diagnosis first — check-engine lights, unknown noises, performance issues — we need to see the car. Diagnostics run $95 and roll into the repair cost if you proceed.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q-5": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you service hybrids and EVs?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. All nine techs are trained on hybrid systems, and four hold current high-voltage certifications for full EV service. We don't replace drive batteries in-house, but everything else — brakes, suspension, coolant, cabin systems, tires — is fully within scope.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q-6": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What if the job is bigger than the quote?",
            "answer": "<p>We stop work and call you. You see the revised scope and price before we continue. If you decide not to proceed, you pay only for the work completed to that point — never more than the original quote for the portion finished.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q-sidebar": {
          "type": "info",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Ready to book?",
            "text": "<p>(555) 408-2170</p><p>Mon–Fri · 7am – 6pm</p><p>Sat · 8am – 2pm</p>"
          }
        }
      },
